Output source of term to an XML comment, one commentand another comment when it does not.
comment 1 ( when $2 contains 'rda' and no $1 or $0): Source of rdaed:P20001 'hasContentType' value is coded '<xsl:value-of select="marc:subfield[@code='2']"/>': lookup the value of rdaed:P20001 in that source, retrieve the IRI and insert it into the data as the direct value of rdaeo:P20001.
comment 2 (when $2 does not contain 'rda' and no $1 or $0): Source of the rdaed:P20001 'hasContentType' value is coded '<xsl:value-of select="marc:subfield[@code='2']"/>': it may be possible to consult that source to retrieve an IRI for the current value of rdaed:P20001.

coded. --TG, 2022-11-11

Construct a value for rdaed:P20071:
"Content Type {336$a value} applies to {336$3 value}"

This has to be done for each $a as these subfields are repeatable; do note that $3 is not repeatable

We are not at present associating the $0 or $1 with a $3 value.

updated --CEY, 2025-04-03
column28:
The essential issue is the identification of the expression or manifestation that is the subject of the output triple(s). If we know that subfield $3 pertains to a subunit of the manifestation in focus, then the information on materials specified can be assigned to the manifestation being described (the superunit), but I think subfield $3 also covers separately published accompanying manifestations or embodied expressions, and then it's tricky.--Gordon 7/8/2024

I think for now it's ok for us to map this provisionally to note on manifestation, removing the "the manifestation's" from the output note. Let's revisit this for Phase II when we start mapping diachronic works/other aggregate types and look at examples to see what else we can do with it. Maybe we could also take a sample of the values we find in $3 here from our output data and see how it looks. -CEY 2025-04-03
